===Etymology===
Latin ''[[Maria]]'', from Greek ''[[Μαρία]]'' (Maria), ''[[Μαριάμ]]'' (Mariam), from Aramaic ''[[מרים]]'' (Maryām), bitter, from a root '''מר''' (<small>MR</small>) meaning to be bitter.  The name corresponds to the Hebrew ''[[מרים]]'' (Miryām), [[Miriam]].

